<div id="review_1039909867" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1039909867" />
    <a title="☺~Tina~☺" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3549398-tina"><img alt="☺~Tina~☺" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1577929193p2/3549398.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1039909867?book_show_action=true">Aug 29, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="☺~Tina~☺" class="user" itemprop="url" name="☺~Tina~☺" href="/user/show/3549398-tina">☺~Tina~☺</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3549398-tina?shelf=bible">bible</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3549398-tina?shelf=affairs">affairs</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3549398-tina?shelf=physical-abuse">physical-abuse</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3549398-tina?shelf=african-american-fiction">african-american-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3549398-tina?shelf=murder">murder</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1039909867" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4545392557733191012"><b>3.5 STARS</b><br/><br/>Interesting read. I was warned that it had a slow start and I&apos;m glad because the first I&apos;ll say about 20% is a little rough. I think it&apos;s a problem with information delivery. It&apos;s so much at the beginning that the transitioning is not smooth and flowing. <br/><br/>Once you get over the hump the story flows and you just keep wonder, okay...where is he going. <br/><br/>The synopsis is a good highlight of the story so I will not repeat that part. I loved all the characters though. Once the author could settle</span>
  <span id="freeText4545392557733191012" style="display:none"><b>3.5 STARS</b><br /><br />Interesting read. I was warned that it had a slow start and I'm glad because the first I'll say about 20% is a little rough. I think it's a problem with information delivery. It's so much at the beginning that the transitioning is not smooth and flowing. <br /><br />Once you get over the hump the story flows and you just keep wonder, okay...where is he going. <br /><br />The synopsis is a good highlight of the story so I will not repeat that part. I loved all the characters though. Once the author could settle down into the story and focus on the characters I felt the story's pull.<br /><br />Yvonne and William are very complexed characters and I see why another book is needed. In this first book, we barely get to scratch the surface of these two or their special kids. But I LOVE the scenes that showed William with his kids. So much of their future is wrapped up in their past that it takes a while to uncover the story so the book ended right when it got really good. I was waiting to see what would happen when Yvonne and William got together. Both of them can't seem to get out of their own way. William it seem is coming around, he's just blind to the end result. These books with people not knowing their true identity can get a little tedious if it drags out to long, hopefully more will be revealed the next book and they can get started on their path. <br /><br />I'll be honest, I still don't quite understand what is going on but I'm looking forward to seeing how this will play out with William, Yvonne and the rest of the players. <br /><br />(I was given a copy of this book in exchange for an honest review.)</span>
  <a data-text-id="4545392557733191012" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


