    <a title="OOSA " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1411473-oosa"><img alt="OOSA " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1307807557p2/1411473.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/30315667?book_show_action=true">Aug 16, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="OOSA " class="user" itemprop="url" name="OOSA " href="/user/show/1411473-oosa">OOSA </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781425787004" href="/book/show/2980385-shadows-of-the-heart">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer30315667" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12912526667721176370"> Shadows of the Heart<br/><br/>Step into the middle of William R. Green&apos;s world-wind of love and destruction, where all he wanted was to reconcile his marriage before he faced his own death. William and Yvonne have been married for many years. To say that their marriage is on the rocks is putting it mild. Yvonne is tired of all her husband&apos;s extramarital affairs and takes matters into her own hands...and abandons her husband and their five children. William has faith that his wife will return to them beca</span>
  <span id="freeText12912526667721176370" style="display:none"> Shadows of the Heart<br /><br />Step into the middle of William R. Green's world-wind of love and destruction, where all he wanted was to reconcile his marriage before he faced his own death. William and Yvonne have been married for many years. To say that their marriage is on the rocks is putting it mild. Yvonne is tired of all her husband's extramarital affairs and takes matters into her own hands...and abandons her husband and their five children. William has faith that his wife will return to them because of his "powers." Will William be able to reconcile with is wife or will he die of a broken heart? <br /><br />"Shadows of the Heart" provides the readers with fantasy, romance, and mystical adventures. It was an interesting read. If you are in the mood for romance, drama and a touch of paranormal, this one is for you. <br /><br /><br />Reviewed by: Nikki </span>
